313.name: Fertility (UN Population Division (2015 revision))
313.description: The total fertility rate is expressed as the average number of children a hypothetical cohort of women would have at the end of their reproductive period if they were subject during their whole lives to the fertility rates of a given period and if they were not subject to mortality. It is expressed as live births per woman.
313.coverage: Global by country and world region (world regions are as defined by the source (the UN))
